The paper deals with combinatorial optimization problems in self-assembly, which suggests that it could belong to the Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) category. The algorithmic nature of the paper and the use of computational complexity theory suggest that it could also belong to the Computational Complexity (cs.CC) category. The paper also deals with geometric aspects of self-assembly, which suggests that it could belong to the Computational Geometry (cs.CG) category. The investigation of the relationship between tile system size and temperature suggests that the paper could belong to the Graph Theory (cs.GT) category. Finally, the use of self-assembly as a model for molecular computation suggests that the paper could belong to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) category.
